attributes.description: Alicon Castalloy manufactures aluminium castings including cylinder heads, support brackets, intake manifolds, crankshafts, and engine brackets for the auto industry. It has a presence in 18 countries and is a part of Alicon Group. The co. was established as Enkei Castalloy Ltd, a joint venture between Pegasus Castalloy Ltd and Enkei Corporation (now Alicon Castalloy), in Japan; one of the largest manufacturers of alloy wheels in the world.
